steps.description: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce. Cut potatoes into ½-inch-thick wedges. Peel garlic; place in the center of a small piece of foil. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper; cinch into a packet. Halve, peel and thinly slice onion.

Toss potatoes on a baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. Roast for 10 minutes. Add garlic foil packet to same sheet. Roast until garlic is browned and softened and potatoes are browned and crispy, 12-15 minutes more.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, 8-10 minutes. Add 1 tsp sugar (2 tsp for 4 servings) and a splash of water; cook, stirring, until onion is caramelized, 2-3 minutes more. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4). Transfer to a small bowl and cover with foil to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

Form beef into two ½-inch-thick patties (four patties for 4 servings), each slightly wider than a burger bun; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for onion over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, 3-5 minutes per side. In the last 2 minutes of cooking, sprinkle each patty with cheese; cover pan to melt cheese.

While patties cook, halve and toast buns. Mash roasted garlic with a fork until smooth. In a small bowl, combine mashed garlic with mayonnaise, ¼ tsp sugar (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of wasabi (taste and add more wasabi if you like). Season with pepper.
Spread bottom buns with horseradish sauce; fill buns with patties and caramelized onions. Divide cheeseburgers and potato wedges between plates. Serve with ketchup on the side for dipping.
